Between 1959 and 1961, a collection of interactive graphical programs had been created 
on the TX-0 experimental computer at MIT. These included Mouse in the Maze and Tic-Tac-Toe.

Graetz, Martin (August 1981). "The origin of Spacewar"
https://archive.org/details/creativecomputing-1981-08/page/n59/mode/2up


